<br>
I was thinking how much cumulative experience we have as players and thought it might be cool to start a thread about combat and grouping tips for the different classes, you know, to maybe help out new players, or players that are new to certain classes.<br>
<br>
(I for one would love to hear any cool bard tricks that Skywise might have picked up over the years.)<br>
<br>
Druid/Ranger tip #1:<br>
This may sound obvious, but I still group with druids &amp; rangers where when the critter gets down on HP's he runs off to let his bud's know he's getting schpanked nastilly, and the druid/ranger is right on their heels continuing to schpank it nastilly! If they would just throw out a &quot;SNARE&quot; in the direction of the critter when he gets below half HP's, two cool things happen. When he gets a notion to go cry to his bud's about the nasty schpankage, he will find his feet stuck to the ground... AND... he'll be so discombobulated about his feet being stuck that he'll conveniently forget to schpank you back whilst you finish him off! ROOT on the other hand (a tactic I see some druids use) will glue a critter's feet to the dirt, but he will still beat on you while you are killing him.<br>
<br>
Buffer tip #1:<br>
If you like to buff the other people in your group before combat, cast the round of buffs on yourself first, then on the other guys. That way, when your buffage wears off you know that any second now all the other people are gonna be whining for a refresh on THEIR buffs, and you can act all omnicient and stuff by re-doing their buffs just as their little icons are blinking. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  They should really appreciate it.<br>
<br>
So lets see more tips here!<br>
<br>
