<br>
I have a bunch of druid tips for another day but the big one is to specialize in a soloing ability (evocation or conjuration).  Being an evoker won't make you ungroupable (in fact I have yet to have a group notice) but being an alterer will darn near make you un-soloable or give you tons of downtime.  Soloing is fast, boring exp.  I think it's important that we maintain the ability to do both since I don't often hear people shouting for a druid in their group.<br>
